# ANNVERO Page Performance Standard

Pilot pattern: `/muhasebe/banka-ekstresi`, `/muhasebe/firma-yonetimi` (thin route shell + deferred workbench). Same standard applies to **every** new or changed route.

## First paint

- Route `page.*` stays a **thin shell**: title, primary controls, skeleton, short “Hazırlanıyor…”.
- Heavy workbenches load via `next/dynamic` (`ssr: false` when client-only) with a loading fallback — no blank white screen.
- Do not statically import Excel/PDF (`xlsx`, `file-saver`, `jszip`, export helpers), OCR/parser/AI/report engines, or large preview tables in the route entry.

## Mount only what is visible

- Closed modals, drawers, accordions, and inactive tabs must **not** mount.
- Tables/charts load when their section is shown (or after first meaningful data).
- Export libraries `import()` only inside the user export/download handler.

## Data

- Prefer `CompanyWorkspace` / shared hooks (`useCompanyList`, `useOptionalCompanyWorkspace`). Do not re-`fetchCompanies` when workspace already has the list.
- No `localStorage` / IndexedDB / heavy sync work in render body; hydrate in `useEffect` or on demand (async), or derive with `useMemo` from workspace.
- Long lists: pagination, windowing, or lazy render — do not hold hundreds of documents in one client state tree without paging.

## UX

- Busy states: skeleton or “Hazırlanıyor…” only — no fake percent.
- Engine preload before an action: button “Hazırlanıyor…”, disable double-submit, safe retry on import failure.
- One-click navigation must still land on a usable shell immediately.

## Checklist (new or refactored route)

- [ ] `page.*` &lt; ~8–10 KB and does not import engines/tables directly
- [ ] Workbench/components split with `dynamic()` + loading UI
- [ ] Inactive tabs/modals gated (`activeTab === …`, `open && …`)
- [ ] Export/OCR/parser/AI via dynamic `import()` on action
- [ ] Workspace reused; no duplicate company fetch
- [ ] No storage/heavy compute in render
- [ ] Lists paged or virtualized when large
- [ ] Smoke: warm nav shell ≤ 1–2 s; no “Rendering…” 5–6 s stall for the shell

## Inventory

Re-run static risk scan after large UI changes:

`node scripts/inventory-page-performance.mjs`
